Unstructured Datasets: Data is not organized in a predefined manner and may require preprocessing before it can be analyzed (e.g., images, audio files).<br>
Semi-Structured Datasets: Data that does not conform strictly to a table but still has some organizational structure (e.g., JSON, XML).<br>
